node.text:
Rediscovering the joy ✨📚👩🏻‍🍳 The book tasting activity was meant for the kids…to try some new literary genres that they wouldn’t normally have chosen. They rotated to different tables and read, discussed, and recommended some new finds. Squeals of excitement and enjoyment were heard throughout the room. 🤗 Many many thanks to @headoverheelsforteaching for creating this amazing resource!

What I didn’t realize was how much I *myself* needed the fun again; something that I‘ve been missing for a while. Nothing fancy really needed…a stack of books on what could’ve been a butcher paper tablecloth, and a willingness to try. And during this single hour, I swear I almost felt the magic coming back…✨

So amongst all of the different protocols, distancing, and constraints that may be put upon your teaching right now, my hope for all of us remains the same: that we find ways to hone our craft, find the fun again, and reinvigorate our love for teaching. 🙏🏼💛 #pandemicteaching #teacherproblems #booktasting #teachingin2021

node.text: Back to School Night, done! ✅ Nerves and sweatiness made me feel like I was suffocating while presenting behind a mask 😰😷, but we made it work. Time to crawl in a hole and sleep for 2 days, before I figure out how I’m going to teach a full 5 days next week…😅 Happy Friday, friends!! We made it! #teachertired #backtoschool #classroom #teachingin2021

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Primary Kind of Life on September 07, 2021. May be an image of office, indoor and text.

node.text:
BACK to SCHOOL! 😄😭 I opened the doors to my classroom last week, with so many mixed emotions…excitement, relief, anxiety, fear, anticipation, dread. I had to literally *drag my feet* to get it all ready, but just for today… I can say that I’m glad to be here. And aside from all of the uncertainty swirling overhead, I’m glad to say that I still find joy in this Happy Place. The lightbulb moments, the laughter, the learning…it’s all here, and thankfully, the little humans are here by my side to share it.

I have no idea what the year ahead holds, but I will never again take the magic of (in-person) classroom teaching for granted. One of my kids said it best…”we don’t HAVE to come to school…we GET to come to school.” 😭😍

Teacher friends, we have been forever changed, for better or worse, and I wish each one of you the best possible school year ever. 🙏🏼 Nothing is easy and many of us are hanging on by a quickly fraying thread, but may you find the light and laughter you deserve, and hopefully…learn to love teaching again. ❤️ #backtoschool #pandemicteaching #teachersofinstagram #teacherstrong #grateful

node.text:
HANDS UP! 🙋🏻‍♀️✋🏼 Last year, we were able to keep doing our favorite “secret handshakes” and high fives, thanks to these signs (made with Astrobrights and some paint sticks). They also made it so much easier for me to see my students raising their *hands* from behind a shield. While I no longer have shields this year, I’ll still be making a class set of these signs because the handshakes and high fives are necessary! All credit for the idea goes to my friend @hello_fifth …a teacher who inspires me everyday!! 

Your turn: tag a teacher friend who inspires you, and head over to @astrobrights for more inspiration and while you’re there, enter their Teachers Helping Teachers contest so you AND a teacher friend will win $2,000 and ALL OF THEIR TEACHER TOOLS! 👯‍♀️🥳🙌🏼🙌🏼Happy back-to-school to all of you!! #teachersofinstagram #colorizeyourclassroom #ad #backtoschool

node.text:
Yes, the paper is very wrinkled. Yes it bothers me tremendously. 🥴 No, I’m not going to redo it. 😂 I came in with wonderful intentions of completely changing my bulletin board this year, but once reality hit…my resolve quickly waned. 

Normally, I’d have a level and some black staples in my hand, so I’m surprising myself here. 🤷🏻‍♀️ But If I had to guess, I’d think it has something to do with the fact that pandemic teaching made me pretty realistic about what matters most and where I want to invest my energies and efforts. And friends, fixing wrinkly bulletin board paper ain’t it (for me). 

So I’m leaving this warped hot mess on my feed as a signpost to remind myself that it really is GOOD ENOUGH. And then I’ll move on to the 438 other things I have to do before school starts.😅 #typeBgotme #typeAteacherspleaseforgiveme #itsfine #goodenough #bulletinboards #backtoschool

node.text:
When your Chromecart “before and after” pics feel like a metaphor for your life. 🤦🏻‍♀️😂 

Photo A:  The cart is beautifully organized. The devices match, the slots are all filled, the teacher is thrilled. 😍🌈💻 Then, 2020-21 happened…….

Photo B: Everything hurts and I’m dying. 😭😩 Nothing matches, the cords are everywhere, and half the devices are nowhere to be found. 🤷🏻‍♀️

So, how does your tech situation look like this year? Have you guys gotten your tech back? Getting new ones? Or patiently waiting? 🙏🏼 And btw, no judgment here, if you are fully stocked. I will celebrate with you because we could all use a win right about now! ❤️ #edtech #edtechteachers #teacherproblems #chromebook #classroom #colorcode #madewithmichaels

WASHI TAPE is from @michaelsstores I get the big rainbow dispenser by Recollections, with all the colors. Use a coupon and your teacher discount!! 🥳

node.text:
MUTE LOCK and VIDEO LOCK on Google Meet 🎤💻🔒: The world sees a couple of new features. Teachers see a bright beacon of hope in a hybrid-teaching-world-gone-mad 🤩✨😂 Rolling out soon is the ability to “mute all” and KEEP them muted, and the ability to turn off everyone’s video with just one click. ✅ 

And while you’re here, I should also mention that you will soon have the ability to SCHEDULE assignments for MULTIPLE CLASSES! Check my “Google Updates”highlight for the details on all the new features rolling out in Google this year on Google Classroom, Forms, Meet, and more! Tell a friend…🥳🙌🏼🙌🏼 #googleclassroom #googleET @google #teacherproblems #remoteteaching #hybridteaching #edtech #backtoschool

node.text:
When HEALING calls…and it tastes like warm malasadas and tropical Mai tai’s, feels like ziplining hundreds of yards over a valley of sweet pineapples, and smells like fresh ocean water lapping the shores of a private beach….you answer the call. Even though it might force you to hike a mile high crater with the sun beating down on your face, it also promises to give you the most majestic view you’ve ever seen, once you arrive. You may have to work a bit for it, but it’s worth it. THIS is what Hawaii did for me, and I will forever be grateful for it. 

If you look at the picture from my previous post, you’d see a worn down human being with nothing left to give. And even though it’s going to take a summer of restoration, I can say that I’m coming back home with a lot more in my tank than I had when I left. 

Mahalo Hawaii for sharing your land, your food, your culture with the world. You left an impression on my soul. ❤️ Teacher peeps, I hope this is a summer of Healing for each one of you, too. Cheers, friends…we made it 👊🏼 #summerbreak #hawaii #teachers #tiredteacher #remoteteaching #hybridteaching

node.text:
✅ Classroom packed 
📁 Files updated 
😵‍💫 Teacher cooked 

You won’t find a cute selfie of me in a packed-up classroom…this is the best I got for a school year that nearly did me in. It feels like the weight of a million expectations is slowly being lifted off my back and honestly, it’s going to take some time to release it. My SOUL is 15-months-exhausted and right now, relief looks a lot more like weeping than celebrating, but it is what it is.

Check my “we made it” highlights (temporarily) for the real, raw feels…😭 Congrats to those who are done! And to those of you who are fighting your way to the finish line, we are all pulling for you.💪🏼 If you need me, I’ll be on the couch, eating Crumbl cookies, taking naps at will, and giving myself the break I so desperately need. Teachers friends, I love and respect each one of you.❤️

#tiredteacher #teacherproblems #remoteteaching #distanceteaching #remotelearning2020 #pandemicteaching #hybridteaching #hyflexteaching #tired

node.text:
That one friend, who took their hate for the drab shields and turned it into something fab. 😂 I should preface by saying that I’m a massive perfectionist and my need for order is extremely high. So if this setup gives you hives, I completely understand it! 👯‍♀️ HOWEVER, none of this hot mess actually bothers me. 🤷🏻‍♀️

This school year, I found myself needing all of the things (big or small) that bring me joy: coffee, cheezits, chocolate, and new packs of flair pens. So I say, “Rainbow-pen-and-origami it up, little friend...find your joy!” And I’m going to leave this picture here on my feed to remind me to find beauty in the chaos. Plus, this just might be the desk of a future teacher...🌈🖍🍎 Now how about you...does this desk drive you crazy? 😨🤣 #pandemicteaching #hybridteaching #teacherproblems #distanceteaching #remotelearning
